Existing tab focus code exists in content-commands.ts (platform/browser-extension/src/browser-commands/content-commands.ts) where `chrome.tabs.update(tabId, { active: true })` and `chrome.windows.update(windowId, { focused: true })` are used. Use the same pattern.

The tab-matching module exports `findAllMatchingTabs(plugin: PluginMeta)` which returns tabs sorted by rank (active+focused first). The handler needs PluginMeta from storage to call this.

For round-robin cycling, maintain a simple in-memory Map<string, number> (pluginName → lastFocusedIndex). On each call, increment the index mod tabCount. Reset when tab count changes. This does NOT need to be persisted — it's ephemeral UI state.

Changes:
1. Add handler function `handleBgOpenPluginTab`:
```typescript
// In-memory round-robin state (ephemeral, not persisted)
const cycleIndex = new Map<string, number>();

const handleBgOpenPluginTab = async (msg: BgMessage): Promise<{ opened: boolean; tabId?: number }> => {
  const pluginName = (msg as { pluginName?: string }).pluginName;
  if (!pluginName) return { opened: false };

  const meta = await getPluginMeta(pluginName); // from plugin-storage.ts
  if (!meta) return { opened: false };

  const tabs = await findAllMatchingTabs(meta);

  if (tabs.length > 0) {
    // Focus existing tab with round-robin cycling
    const prevIdx = cycleIndex.get(pluginName) ?? -1;
    const nextIdx = (prevIdx + 1) % tabs.length;
    cycleIndex.set(pluginName, nextIdx);
    const tab = tabs[nextIdx];
    if (tab.id !== undefined) {
      await chrome.tabs.update(tab.id, { active: true });
      if (tab.windowId !== undefined) {
        await chrome.windows.update(tab.windowId, { focused: true });
      }
      return { opened: true, tabId: tab.id };
    }
  }

  // No matching tabs — open homepage if available
  if (meta.homepage) {
    const newTab = await chrome.tabs.create({ url: meta.homepage });
    return { opened: true, tabId: newTab.id };
  }

  return { opened: false };
};
```

2. Add to dispatch map:
```typescript
'bg:openPluginTab': handleBgOpenPluginTab,
```

3. In bridge.ts, add the bridge function:
